Few people are aware@#%^&*('aware', 'ROOT', 'R')	
that the federal government lends almost as much money@#%^&*('lends', 'aware', 'U')	('as', 'borrows', 'U')	
as it borrows.@#%^&*('borrows', 'lends', 'U')	
From 1980 to 1988,@#%^&*('1988', 'issued', 'U')	
while federal budget deficits totaled $1.41 trillion,@#%^&*('totaled', 'issued', 'U')	
the government issued $394 billion of new direct loans and an additional $756 billion of new primary loan guarantees.@#%^&*('issued', 'ROOT', 'R')	
These figures omit secondary guarantees, deposit insurance, and the activities of Government-Sponsored Enterprises@#%^&*('omit', 'ROOT', 'R')	('a', 'concern', 'U')	
(a huge concern in its own right,@#%^&*('concern', 'Enterprises', 'U')	
as detailed on this page May 3).@#%^&*('detailed', 'right', 'U')	
Federal credit programs date back to the New Deal,@#%^&*('programs', 'meant', 'U')	('programs', 'break', 'U')	('date', 'ROOT', 'R')	
and were meant to break even financially.@#%^&*('meant', 'date', 'U')	
Since the 1950s, federal lending has experienced extraordinary growth in credit volume, subsidy rates, and policy applications,@#%^&*('lending', 'spurred', 'U')	('experienced', 'ROOT', 'R')	
spurred on by the growth of government in general and budget gimmicks and deceptive management in particular.@#%^&*('spurred', 'experienced', 'U')	('management', 'experienced', 'U')	
As we will see,@#%^&*('see', 'show', 'U')	
many of these obligations don't show up as part of the federal deficit.@#%^&*('show', 'ROOT', 'R')	
But recent events indicate@#%^&*('indicate', 'ROOT', 'R')	
that federal credit is out of control.@#%^&*('is', 'indicate', 'U')	
Student loan defaults remain high at about 12%,@#%^&*('remain', 'ROOT', 'R')	
and the program has been rocked by allegations of fraud and mismanagement.@#%^&*('rocked', 'remain', 'U')	
Farmers Home Administration@#%^&*('Administration', 'loans', 'U')	
(FmHA)@#%^&*('FmHA', 'loans', 'U')	
loans have turned into de facto giveaway programs;@#%^&*('turned', 'ROOT', 'R')	
losses over the next three years are expected to exceed $20 billion.@#%^&*('expected', 'turned', 'U')	
Defaults on Veterans Affairs loan guarantees have quadrupled in the past eight years.@#%^&*('quadrupled', 'ROOT', 'R')	
Last month, the General Accounting Office reported@#%^&*('reported', 'ROOT', 'R')	
that defaults in Federal Housing Administration guarantees were five times as high@#%^&*('high', 'reported', 'U')	('as', 'estimated', 'U')	
as previously estimated,@#%^&*('estimated', 'high', 'U')	('estimated', 'high', 'U')	
and that FHA's equity fell to minus $2.9 billion.@#%^&*('fell', 'high', 'U')	('fell', 'high', 'U')	('fell', 'estimated', 'U')	
GAO's findings are particularly troubling@#%^&*('troubling', 'ROOT', 'R')	
because the FHA has about $300 billion in obligations outstanding@#%^&*('FHA', 'considered', 'U')	('has', 'troubling', 'U')	
and had previously been considered one of the most financially secure credit programs.@#%^&*('considered', 'troubling', 'U')	('considered', 'has', 'U')	
Scores of other credit programs,@#%^&*('Scores', 'visible', 'U')	
subsidizing agriculture, small business, exporters, defense, energy, transportation and others,@#%^&*('subsidizing', 'visible', 'U')	
are less visible but in no better shape.@#%^&*('visible', 'ROOT', 'R')	
If the programs continue their present path,@#%^&*('continue', 'staggering', 'U')	('the', 'losses', 'U')	
the potential government losses are staggering:@#%^&*('staggering', 'ROOT', 'R')	
The federal government holds $222 billion in direct loans outstanding@#%^&*('government', 'backs', 'U')	('holds', 'staggering', 'U')	
and backs an additional $550 billion in primary guarantees.@#%^&*('backs', 'staggering', 'U')	('backs', 'holds', 'U')	
(Secondary guarantees of pools of FHA- and VA-backed loans by the agency@#%^&*('guarantees', 'internal', 'U')	('guarantees', 'generic', 'U')	('loans', 'internal', 'U')	
known as Ginnie Mae@#%^&*('known', 'agency', 'U')	('as', 'causes', 'U')	('Mae', 'exceed', 'U')	
currently exceed $330 billion.)@#%^&*('exceed', 'causes', 'U')	
Although external events have contributed to the morass,@#%^&*('contributed', 'causes', 'U')	('the', 'principal', 'U')	
the principal causes of the current crisis are internal and generic to all programs.@#%^&*('causes', 'known', 'U')	('internal', 'ROOT', 'R')	
To reduce the risks@#%^&*('reduce', 'Use', 'U')	
while still retaining the legitimate benefits@#%^&*('retaining', 'reduce', 'U')	
these programs can provide,@#%^&*('provide', 'benefits', 'U')	
credit policy must:@#%^&*('policy', 'Use', 'U')	('must', 'Use', 'U')	
1. Use credit@#%^&*('Use', 'ROOT', 'R')	
to improve the operation of capital markets,@#%^&*('improve', 'Use', 'U')	
not to provide subsidies.@#%^&*('provide', 'improve', 'U')	
There is a fundamental conflict@#%^&*('is', 'ROOT', 'R')	
between providing a subsidy@#%^&*('providing', 'conflict', 'U')	
and maintaining the integrity of a credit program.@#%^&*('maintaining', 'conflict', 'U')	('maintaining', 'providing', 'U')	
If the program is meant to provide a subsidy,@#%^&*('meant', 'defeats', 'U')	
collecting the debt defeats the original goal.@#%^&*('defeats', 'ROOT', 'R')	
Thus, subsidized loans tend to turn into giveaway programs, with increasing subsidy and default rates over time.@#%^&*('tend', 'ROOT', 'R')	
To avoid this problem,@#%^&*('avoid', 'issue', 'U')	
government should issue credit@#%^&*('issue', 'ROOT', 'R')	
only if it intends to use every legal method@#%^&*('intends', 'issue', 'U')	('to', 'collect', 'U')	
to collect.@#%^&*('collect', 'use', 'U')	
In contrast, credit programs can be appropriate tools@#%^&*('tools', 'ROOT', 'R')	('to', 'improve', 'U')	
to improve the operation of capital markets.@#%^&*('improve', 'tools', 'U')	
For example, legal restrictions on interstate banking once inhibited the supply of credit to the agricultural sector.@#%^&*('inhibited', 'ROOT', 'R')	
Farm lending was enacted@#%^&*('lending', 'correct', 'U')	('enacted', 'ROOT', 'R')	
to correct this problem@#%^&*('correct', 'enacted', 'U')	
by providing a reliable flow of lendable funds.@#%^&*('providing', 'correct', 'U')	
However, this in no way justifies the huge government subsidies and losses on such loans.@#%^&*('justifies', 'ROOT', 'R')	
Credit policy should separate these two competing objectives@#%^&*('policy', 'eliminate', 'U')	('separate', 'ROOT', 'R')	
and eliminate aspects@#%^&*('eliminate', 'separate', 'U')	('aspects', 'provide', 'U')	
that provide the subsidy.@#%^&*('provide', 'aspects', 'U')	
For example, student loans currently attempt to subsidize college attendance and mitigate problems@#%^&*('attempt', 'ROOT', 'R')	
created by the fact@#%^&*('created', 'problems', 'U')	
that students' future earnings are not accepted as collateral.@#%^&*('accepted', 'created', 'U')	
The program provides highly subsidized loans to any student@#%^&*('provides', 'ROOT', 'R')	('student', 'family', 'U')	
whose family earns less than a particular amount.@#%^&*('earns', 'student', 'U')	
High default rates, a low interest rate, and government coverage of all interest costs@#%^&*('costs', 'ROOT', 'R')	
while the student is in school@#%^&*('is', 'costs', 'U')	
make program costs extremely high.@#%^&*('make', 'is', 'U')	
Families@#%^&*('Families', 'need', 'U')	('Families', 'make', 'U')	
that do not need the loan@#%^&*('need', 'Families', 'U')	
can make money@#%^&*('make', 'ROOT', 'R')	
simply by putting the loan in the bank@#%^&*('simply', 'make', 'U')	('putting', 'make', 'U')	
and paying it back@#%^&*('paying', 'make', 'U')	('paying', 'putting', 'U')	
when the student graduates.@#%^&*('graduates', 'paying', 'U')	
In contrast, a student loan program@#%^&*('contrast', 'allow', 'U')	('program', 'meant', 'U')	('program', 'correct', 'U')	('program', 'allow', 'U')	
that was meant solely to correct capital-market imperfections@#%^&*('meant', 'program', 'U')	
would allow loans for any student,@#%^&*('allow', 'ROOT', 'R')	
regardless of family income,@#%^&*('income', 'allow', 'U')	
at market or near-market rates.@#%^&*('rates', 'allow', 'U')	
While the student was in school,@#%^&*('was', 'paid', 'U')	
interest costs would either be paid by the student@#%^&*('costs', 'added', 'U')	('paid', 'ROOT', 'R')	
or added to the loan balance.@#%^&*('added', 'paid', 'U')	
This program,@#%^&*('program', 'reduce', 'U')	('program', 'target', 'U')	
combined with cash grants to needy students,@#%^&*('combined', 'program', 'U')	
would reduce program costs@#%^&*('reduce', 'ROOT', 'R')	
and much more effectively target the intended beneficiaries.@#%^&*('target', 'reduce', 'U')	
2. Provide better incentives.@#%^&*('Provide', 'ROOT', 'R')	
Given the structure of most credit programs,@#%^&*('Given', 'surprising', 'U')	('it', 'surprising', 'U')	
it is surprising that default rates are not even higher.@#%^&*('surprising', 'ROOT', 'R')	
Guarantee rates are typically 100%,@#%^&*('%', 'ROOT', 'R')	
giving lenders little reason@#%^&*('giving', '%', 'U')	
to screen customers carefully.@#%^&*('screen', 'reason', 'U')	
Reducing those rates moderately@#%^&*('Reducing', 'provide', 'U')	
(say, to 75%)@#%^&*('to', 'Reducing', 'U')	
would still provide substantial assistance to borrowers.@#%^&*('provide', 'ROOT', 'R')	
But it would also encourage lenders to choose more creditworthy customers,@#%^&*('encourage', 'ROOT', 'R')	('lenders', 'go', 'U')	
and go a long way toward reducing defaults.@#%^&*('go', 'encourage', 'U')	('go', 'choose', 'U')	
For example, the Small Business Administration has had reasonable success@#%^&*('had', 'ROOT', 'R')	
in reducing both guarantee rates and default rates in its Preferred Lenders' Program.@#%^&*('reducing', 'had', 'U')	
Borrowers' incentives are equally skewed.@#%^&*('skewed', 'ROOT', 'R')	
Since the government has a dismal record@#%^&*('has', 'low', 'U')	
of collecting bad debts,@#%^&*('collecting', 'record', 'U')	
the costs to the borrower of defaulting are usually low.@#%^&*('low', 'ROOT', 'R')	
In addition, it is often possible to obtain a new government loan@#%^&*('possible', 'ROOT', 'R')	
even if existing debts are not paid off.@#%^&*('paid', 'obtain', 'U')	
Simple policy prescriptions in this case would be to improve debt collection@#%^&*('be', 'ROOT', 'R')	
(taking the gloves off contracted collection agencies)@#%^&*
and to deny new credit to defaulters.@#%^&*('deny', 'be', 'U')	('deny', 'improve', 'U')	
These provisions would be difficult to enforce for a program@#%^&*('difficult', 'ROOT', 'R')	
intended to provide a subsidy,@#%^&*('intended', 'program', 'U')	
but would be reasonable and effective devices for programs@#%^&*('devices', 'difficult', 'U')	('programs', 'attempt', 'U')	('programs', 'offset', 'U')	
that attempt to offset market imperfections.@#%^&*('attempt', 'programs', 'U')	
3. Record the true costs of credit programs in the federal budget.@#%^&*('Record', 'ROOT', 'R')	
Since the budget measures cash flow,@#%^&*('measures', 'treated', 'U')	('a', 'loan', 'U')	
a new $1 direct loan is treated as a $1 expenditure,@#%^&*('treated', 'ROOT', 'R')	
even though at least part of the loan will be paid back.@#%^&*('paid', 'treated', 'U')	
Loan guarantees don't appear at all@#%^&*('appear', 'ROOT', 'R')	
until the borrower defaults,@#%^&*('defaults', 'appear', 'U')	
so new guarantees do not raise the deficit,@#%^&*('so', 'appear', 'U')	('raise', 'appear', 'U')	
even though they create future liabilities for the government.@#%^&*('create', 'raise', 'U')	
By converting an expenditure or loan to a guarantee,@#%^&*('converting', 'ensure', 'U')	
the government can ensure the same flow of resources@#%^&*('government', 'reduce', 'U')	('ensure', 'ROOT', 'R')	
and reduce the current deficit.@#%^&*('reduce', 'ensure', 'U')	
Predictably, guarantees outstanding have risen by $130 billion since 1985,@#%^&*('risen', 'ROOT', 'R')	
while direct loans outstanding have fallen by $30 billion.@#%^&*('fallen', 'risen', 'U')	
The true budgetary cost of a credit subsidy is the discounted value of the net costs to government.@#%^&*('value', 'ROOT', 'R')	
This figure could be estimated@#%^&*('estimated', 'ROOT', 'R')	
using techniques@#%^&*('using', 'estimated', 'U')	
employed by private lenders@#%^&*('employed', 'techniques', 'U')	
to forecast losses,@#%^&*('losses', 'employed', 'U')	
or determined@#%^&*('determined', 'techniques', 'U')	('determined', 'employed', 'U')	
by selling loans to private owners@#%^&*('selling', 'determined', 'U')	
(without federal guarantees).@#%^&*('without', 'selling', 'U')	
Neither technique is perfect,@#%^&*('perfect', 'ROOT', 'R')	
but both are better than the current system,@#%^&*('better', 'perfect', 'U')	('system', 'misstates', 'U')	
which misstates the costs of new credit programs by amounts@#%^&*('misstates', 'system', 'U')	('amounts', 'vary', 'U')	('amounts', 'average', 'U')	
that vary substantially@#%^&*('vary', 'amounts', 'U')	
and average about $20 billion annually,@#%^&*('average', 'amounts', 'U')	('average', 'vary', 'U')	
according to the Congressional Budget Office.@#%^&*('to', 'misstates', 'U')	('Office', 'misstates', 'U')	
A budget@#%^&*('budget', 'reflected', 'U')	('budget', 'let', 'U')	('budget', 'know', 'U')	
that reflected the real costs of lending@#%^&*('reflected', 'budget', 'U')	('costs', 'eliminate', 'U')	
would eliminate incentives@#%^&*('eliminate', 'reflected', 'U')	('incentives', 'convert', 'U')	
to convert spending or lending programs to guarantees@#%^&*('convert', 'eliminate', 'U')	
and would let taxpayers know@#%^&*('let', 'budget', 'U')	('let', 'reflected', 'U')	('know', 'ROOT', 'R')	
what Congress is committing them to.@#%^&*('committing', 'know', 'U')	
4. Impose standard accounting and administrative practices.@#%^&*('Impose', 'ROOT', 'R')	
Creative accounting is a hallmark of federal credit.@#%^&*('hallmark', 'ROOT', 'R')	
Many agencies roll over their debt,@#%^&*('roll', 'ROOT', 'R')	
paying off delinquent loans@#%^&*('paying', 'roll', 'U')	
by issuing new loans,@#%^&*('issuing', 'paying', 'U')	
or converting defaulted loan guarantees into direct loans.@#%^&*('converting', 'roll', 'U')	('converting', 'paying', 'U')	
In any case, they avoid having to write off the loans.@#%^&*('avoid', 'ROOT', 'R')	
Some agencies simply keep bad loans on the books;@#%^&*('keep', 'ROOT', 'R')	
as late as 1987, the Export-Import Bank held in its portfolio at face value loans@#%^&*('as', 'books', 'U')	('late', 'books', 'U')	('as', 'books', 'U')	('1987', 'books', 'U')	
made to Cuba in the 1950s.@#%^&*('made', 'loans', 'U')	
More seriously, FmHA has carried several billion dollars of defaulted loans at face value.@#%^&*('carried', 'ROOT', 'R')	
Until GAO's recent audit, FHA books had not been subject to a complete external audit in 15 years.@#%^&*('subject', 'ROOT', 'R')	
The administration of federal credit should closely parallel private lending practices,@#%^&*('parallel', 'ROOT', 'R')	
including the development of a loan loss reserve and regular outside audits.@#%^&*('development', 'practices', 'U')	
Establishing these practices would permit earlier identification of emerging financial crises,@#%^&*('Establishing', 'provide', 'U')	('Establishing', 'reduce', 'U')	('permit', 'ROOT', 'R')	
provide better information for loan sales and budgeting decisions,@#%^&*('provide', 'permit', 'U')	
and reduce fraud.@#%^&*('reduce', 'permit', 'U')	
Government lending was not intended to be a way@#%^&*('intended', 'ROOT', 'R')	('to', 'obfuscate', 'U')	
to obfuscate spending figures,@#%^&*('obfuscate', 'way', 'U')	
hide fraudulent activity,@#%^&*('hide', 'way', 'U')	('hide', 'obfuscate', 'U')	
or provide large subsidies.@#%^&*('provide', 'way', 'U')	('provide', 'obfuscate', 'U')	
The reforms@#%^&*('reforms', 'provide', 'U')	
described above@#%^&*('described', 'reforms', 'U')	
would provide a more limited, but clearer, safer and ultimately more useful role for government as a lender.@#%^&*('provide', 'ROOT', 'R')	
Without such reforms,@#%^&*('reforms', 'continue', 'U')	
credit programs will continue to be a large-scale, high-risk proposition for taxpayers.@#%^&*('continue', 'ROOT', 'R')	
